
// This Hyperlambda code demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a collection. It retrieves nodes specified by expressions from the [.arguments] node, including [limit], [offset], [order], and [direction], and adds them to the [data.read] node. This is useful for dynamically constructing a node set based on input arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
